name: The Sandlot
summary: In the summer of 1962, a new kid in town is taken under the wing of a young baseball prodigy and his rowdy team, resulting in many adventures.

name: M.S. Dhoni: The Untold Story
summary: The untold story of

name: The Blind Side
summary: The story of Michael Oher, a homeless and traumatized boy who became an All American football player and first round NFL draft pick with the help of a caring woman and her family.

name: Huo yuanjia
summary: A biography of Chinese Martial Arts Master Huo Yuanjia, who is the founder and spiritual guru of the Jin Wu Sports Federation.

name: The Lives of Others
summary: In 1984 East Berlin, an agent of the secret police, conducting surveillance on a writer and his lover, finds himself becoming increasingly absorbed by their lives.

name: Jodaeiye Nader az Simin
summary: A married couple are faced with a difficult decision - to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer's disease.

name: Reservoir Dogs
summary: When a simple jewelry heist goes horribly wrong, the surviving criminals begin to suspect that one of them is a police informant.

name: Yjinb
summary: A crafty ronin comes to a town divided by two criminal gangs and decides to play them against each other to free the town.

name: Room
summary: Held captive for years in an enclosed space, a woman and her young son finally gain their freedom, allowing the boy to experience the outside world for the first time.

name: Gangs of Wasseypur
summary: A clash between Sultan and Shahid Khan leads to the expulsion of Khan from Wasseypur, and ignites a deadly blood feud spanning three generations.

name: Heat
summary: A group of professional bank robbers start to feel the heat from police when they unknowingly leave a clue at their latest heist.

name: Die Hard
summary: An NYPD officer tries to save his wife and several others taken hostage by German terrorists during a Christmas party at the Nakatomi Plaza in Los Angeles.

name: The Great Escape
summary: Allied prisoners of war plan for several hundred of their number to escape from a German camp during World War II.

name: On the Waterfront
summary: An ex-prize fighter turned longshoreman struggles to stand up to his corrupt union bosses.

name: Dial M for Murder
summary: A tennis player frames his unfaithful wife for first-degree murder after she inadvertently hinders his plan to kill her.

name: Ah-ga-ssi
summary: A woman is hired as a handmaiden to a Japanese heiress, but secretly she is involved in a plot to defraud her.

name: Baby
summary: An elite counter-intelligence unit learns of a plot, masterminded by a maniacal madman. With the clock ticking, it's up to them to track the terrorists' international tentacles and prevent them from striking at the heart of India.

name: Il buono, il brutto, il cattivo
summary: A bounty hunting scam joins two men in an uneasy alliance against a third in a race to find a fortune in gold buried in a remote cemetery.

name: Once Upon a Time in the West
summary: A mysterious stranger with a harmonica joins forces with a notorious desperado to protect a beautiful widow from a ruthless assassin working for the railroad.

name: Per qualche dollaro in pi
summary: Two bounty hunters with the same intentions team up to track down a Western outlaw.

name: Unforgiven
summary: Retired Old West gunslinger William Munny reluctantly takes on one last job, with the help of his old partner and a young man.

name: The Treasure of the Sierra Madre
summary: Fred Dobbs and Bob Curtin, two Americans searching for work in Mexico, convince an old prospector to help them mine for gold in the Sierra Madre Mountains.

name: The General
summary: When Union spies steal an engineer's beloved locomotive, he pursues it single-handedly and straight through enemy lines.

name: Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid
summary: Wyoming, early 1900s. Butch Cassidy and The Sundance Kid are the leaders of a band of outlaws. After a train robbery goes wrong they find themselves on the run with a posse hard on their heels. Their solution - escape to Bolivia.

name: The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance
summary: A senator, who became famous for killing a notorious outlaw, returns for the funeral of an old friend and tells the truth about his deed.

name: The Revenant
summary: A frontiersman on a fur trading expedition in the 1820s fights for survival after being mauled by a bear and left for dead by members of his own hunting team.

name: Dances with Wolves
summary: Lieutenant John Dunbar, assigned to a remote western Civil War outpost, befriends wolves and Indians, making him an intolerable aberration in the military.

name: The Wild Bunch
summary: An aging group of outlaws look for one last big score as the "traditional" American West is disappearing around them.

name: Per un pugno di dollari
summary: A wandering gunfighter plays two rival families against each other in a town torn apart by greed, pride, and revenge.

name: Rio Bravo
summary: A small-town sheriff in the American West enlists the help of a cripple, a drunk, and a young gunfighter in his efforts to hold in jail the brother of the local bad guy.

name: The Searchers
summary: An American Civil War veteran embarks on a journey to rescue his niece from the Comanches.

name: High Noon
summary: A town Marshal, despite the disagreements of his newlywed bride and the townspeople around him, must face a gang of deadly killers alone at high noon when the gang leader, an outlaw he sent up years ago, arrives on the noon train.

name: The Outlaw Josey Wales
summary: A Missouri farmer joins a Confederate guerrilla unit and winds up on the run from the Union soldiers who murdered his family.
